valueObject

public static final OWLObjectProperty valueObject
Supposed to be used whenever some Binding should refer to some (constant) individual, which is to be used as the value for the parameter. Since it is declared as an object property it is not similar to valueData. The latter represents a constant value by means of an XML literal (independent of the syntax and semantics if this literal), whereas this property refers to some OWL individual.

ThisPerform

public static final Perform ThisPerform
A special-purpose object, used to refer, at runtime, to the execution instance of the enclosing process whose definition it occurs in.
